1. ACCEPTANCE OF TERMS

By installing or using PAiA ("the Software"), you agree to be bound by
the terms of this End User License Agreement ("Agreement"). If you do
not agree, do not install or use the Software.

2. LICENSE GRANT

Subject to the terms of this Agreement and your payment of the
applicable fees (if any), [LEGAL NAME] grants you a non-exclusive,
non-transferable, revocable license to install and use the Software:

   (a) FREE TIER: for personal, non-commercial use, on any number of
       devices you personally own. The free tier does not include the
       Pro features described in the product's pricing page.

   (b) PRO TIER (subscription): for personal or commercial use during
       the period covered by your active subscription, on up to one
       device per active seat purchased.

   (c) LIFETIME TIER: for personal or commercial use, in perpetuity,
       on up to three devices that you personally own. The Lifetime
       tier includes all minor updates indefinitely and all major
       updates released within two years of purchase.

3. RESTRICTIONS

You may not:

   - Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the Software, except
     to the extent expressly permitted by applicable law.
   - Rent, lease, sublicense, or distribute the Software to third
     parties.
   - Remove or alter copyright, trademark, or other proprietary notices.
   - Use the Software to build a competing product.
   - Bypass the licensing or trial mechanisms.

4. LOCAL DATA AND PRIVACY

The Software runs locally on your computer. Your conversations, voice
recordings, screen captures, and uploaded documents are processed
entirely on your device and are not transmitted to [LEGAL NAME] or its
servers.

The Software may make optional outbound network connections to:

   - Your local Ollama daemon (loopback interface only)
   - Hugging Face CDN, for downloading speech and TTS models on first use
   - Tesseract OCR data CDN, for downloading language models on first use
   - GitHub Releases, for auto-update checks (configurable)
   - DuckDuckGo, only when you explicitly run a web search command
   - Cloud LLM providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.), only if you opt in
     and configure your own API key

A current and complete list is available at https://paia.app/privacy.

5. THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS

The Software incorporates open-source libraries listed in the
THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md file included with the Software. Each
third-party component is governed by its own license, which is
preserved alongside the Software.

6. PAYMENT, REFUNDS, AND SUBSCRIPTIONS

   (a) Pro and Lifetime tier purchases are processed by our payment
       provider, [LemonSqueezy / Stripe], who acts as the merchant of
       record where applicable.

   (b) Subscription fees are charged in advance for the term selected
       at checkout (monthly or annually). Subscriptions auto-renew
       unless cancelled.

   (c) You may cancel a subscription at any time from your customer
       portal. Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current
       billing period. No refunds are issued for partial periods.

   (d) For Lifetime purchases, [LEGAL NAME] offers a refund within
       thirty (30) days of purchase, no questions asked.

   (e) After a refund, the corresponding license becomes invalid for
       new activations. Existing local installations continue to work
       until the next time the Software verifies the license.

7. UPDATES

   (a) The Software may include an auto-update feature that checks
       for and installs new versions. You may disable this feature in
